title: MMS, Newly open areas along the Alaskan Coastline for Offshore drilling, US, March 31, 2010
name: MMS, Newly open areas along the Alaskan Coastline for Offshore drilling, US, March 31, 2010
description:
The shapefile shows what MMS (Minerals Management Service) of the U.S. Interior Dept calls as OPDs (Official Protracted Areas) that are now open for Oil and Natural gas exploration in Alaska.

The Obama Administration will announce the opening of formerly "forbidden" areas along the Pacific, Atlantic and Alaskan coasts for off-shore drilling. This is a continuation of the off-shore drilling plan announced by previous administration. Look elsewhere on Finder! for more GIS files associated with Offshore drilling. Keyword search = "offshore drilling".

author.source: MMS (Offshore Minerals Management) website of the U.S. Interior Dept.
